l as Parasara's list. If he does not "fit" in your "scheme of evolutionary =
Avatars", then your concept is possibly wrong and avataras are perhaps not =
"evolutionary" as you theorize.
=A0
Secondly, as per Parasara,
 Buddha corr=
esponds to Mercury, who personifies logical mind and the spirit of investig=
ation and comprehension. Logical mind and its spirit of comprehension are i=
nherently fallible. Even a perfected spirit of comprehension is not capable=
 of grasping the Absolute Reality completely, for it is beyond comprehensio=
n. So, no wonder it simplifies the Incomprehensible in an attempt to compre=
hend! That is what Buddha ended up doing. However, logical mind has a great=
 appeal in the Age of Reason in this Kali yuga. No wonder Buddha was/is/wil=
l be a great spiritual force in this world in this age.
=A0
*=A0=A0=A0=A0=
=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *
=A0
If you dismiss Parasara's linking of=
 planets to avataras as a possible corruption, are you absolutely sure that=
 the verses of SB you are relying on are perfect? (In any case, it's a diff=
erent matter that you are only taking some SB verses and ignoring some as I=
 showed!.)
=A0
The bottomline as far as I am concerned is that Pararsara's =
list actually makes amazingly coherent esoteric sense. The nature of each a=
spect of consciousness (e.g. Buddha - spirit of comprehension, Saturn - spi=
rit of patience & persistence, Venus - spirit of happiness etc) and the sto=
ry of
 corresponding avatara DOES have a highly meaningful connection, esot=
erically speaking. After all, esoterically is how you really need to unders=
tand any higher scriptures and notions in them.
=A0
If we take scriptures l=
iterally instead and draw lopsided conclusions, some would conclude that Sh=
iva is the "supreme" one and other deities are "inferior"; some would concl=
ude that Surya is the "supreme" one and other deities are "inferior"; and s=
o on.
=A0
*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *
=A0
On a differen=
t note, someone may think that Kali, being Aadyaa, is superior to Tara and =
like Kali more. But, some learned yogis have declared them to be essentiall=
y the same and some scriptures even prohibited differentiating between them=
. As I see it, the difference between them is too subtle for even rishis to=
 clearly comprehend. People seeing
 some significant difference between the=
m are, I am afraid, merely projecting their own conditioning. Same in the c=
ase of Krishna and Rama. Both were=A0 perfectly detached and fully divine k=
arma yogis.
=A0
If we think about it, perfected mind (paramatma aspect repr=
esented by Moon) and soul (paramatma aspect represented by Sun) are not rea=
lly that different. So I am afraid Krishna and Rama are not that different,=
 though the specifics of their stories may be different.
=A0
One last word =
though. If someone truly believes that Krishna is superior to Rama and wors=
hips Krishna (or vice versa!), I am very happy for such a person. My argume=
nts are more for the sake of sharing thinking/knowledge and pushing the bou=
ndaries of understanding in the long run, than changing the minds of anyone=
 in the short run. In the end, everyone of us will have to go through one's=
 own cycles of various tamasik, rajasik and saattwik stages of evolution be=
fore one starts grasping some fistfuls of Reality. These concepts are too s=
ubtle for anyone to convince others or be absolutely confident oneself!
