 <br>*        *   &n=
bsp;    *<br> <br>Now, let us remember one basic thing.=
 Soul in us, mind in us, energy in us,
 learning spirit in us, wisdom in us=
, happiness in us, discipline/patience in us - all these are different mani=
festations of the same Self. However, when Self manifests as these differen=
t aspects, it has different qualities and plays different roles. There is n=
o comparison between them.<br> <br>We MAY focus on one aspect of us fi=
rst, perfect it and then perfect other aspects through it. But, we need bal=
ance between all aspects in the end. Similarly, these different aspects of =
Supreme Being are incomparable and are in a balance working together in the=
 Cosmos.<br> <br>*        * &n=
bsp;      *<br> <br>One who is fascinated by =
the qualities of soul may like the story that demonstrates how soul operate=
s; one who is fascinated by the qualities of mind may like the story that d=
emonstrates how mind operates, and one who is fascinated by the qualities o=
f wisdom may like the story that
 demonstrates how wisdom operates. And so =
on. But this is just a matter of taste and subjective preference.<br> =
